<br>
It seems we're going to have to quantify this as different people have differing ideas as to what &quot;reasonable&quot; is.<br>
<br>
Personal Pics: No wider than 130 pixels, no higher than 150 pixels. The file size must be 20 KB or smaller.<br>
<br>
Signatures: No wider than 468 pixels, no higher than 60 pixels. The file size must be 20 KB or smaller. Any assosciated text should be 120 characters or less (including spaces).<br>
<br>
If you signature or personal photo image exceeds these specifications, please uncheck the &quot;Include...&quot; options that EZBoard provides when posting.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It's okay if either your personal picture or signature image is over 20k as long as all the images do NOT add up to over 40k.<br>
<br>
Also, do NOT ask us to tell you if your image is okay. The limits are CLEARLY explained and everyone here is more than capable of taking two seconds of their time to check themselves. <br>
<br>
First of all, if you're testing your sig or personal picture DO NOT start a new thread. DO NOT post in another topic testing it. Simply reply to something, but check the preview option before sending the message. Then you can check to see if it shows up. That way you don't have to waste our time with pointless messages.<br>
<br>
Also, to check the file size and the size dimensions (if using IE) simply right click the image, and go to properties. It has the file size and dimensions. If they are over the limits, then you need to change them. Netscape and other browsers should have some similar function. Besides, all of us here should have some sort of image program, so you can always check the dimensions and size in there. <p><table width=100% border=0>
